- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper discusses combinatorial coding. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is mentioned in the abstract as one of the points of view used in the theory. 
- cs.SD (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with multilinear algebra and symmetric tensors. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also less likely but could be relevant as linear codes are used in error-correcting codes, which are important in machine learning.
